Lesson 1 – The Digital World: Where Do CS and IT Meet?

Do Now What you'll learn Key Vocabulary Activities Plenary

Do Now

Match each statement to Computer Science or IT.

1. Designs and builds programs.
Answer: Computer Science.
2. Uses software to analyse business data.
Answer: Information Technology.
3. Understands algorithms and logic.
Answer: Computer Science.
4. Creates digital graphics or presentations.
Answer: Information Technology.

What you'll learn today

By the end of this lesson, you will be able to:

  • Understand what Computer Science and IT mean.
  • Spot real examples of each in everyday life.
  • Think about which one suits you best.

How you'll know you've got it

  • Explain the difference between making technology and using technology.
  • Name one job for each subject.
  • Say which subject you prefer and why.

Key Vocabulary

Algorithm — steps to solve a problem (CS).
Data — raw facts that can be processed (IT).
Software — programs that run on computers.
Hardware — physical components of a computer.
Digital Literacy — confident, safe use of digital tools.

Main Activities

CS Track – Code a Turtle

  1. Open Python (or Turtle online).
  2. Draw a square with a loop.
  3. Personalise with colour and your name.
import turtle
t = turtle.Turtle()
for _ in range(4):
    t.forward(100)
    t.right(90)

IT Track – Build a Mini Survey

  1. Create a Microsoft Form with 3 questions.
  2. Collect class responses.
  3. Use the dashboard to add a chart.
  • Which clubs should run at lunch?
  • Preferred device for homework?
  • What helps you learn best?

Compare & Reflect

  • Which task did you prefer?
  • What skills did each require?
  • Where might both skillsets combine in a job?

Plenary – Hands‑Up Task

  • 🟥 Hands up if you’d pick Computer Science (building technology).
  • 🟦 Hands up if you’d pick IT (using and presenting technology).
  • 🟨 Hands up if you’d like to do both — you enjoy creating and using technology.
  • 🟩 Hands up if you’re still unsure — we’ll discuss what might help you decide.
